            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I don’t bring a whole lot of expert opinion to bear on TV shows, but I know that a) Mad Men has shown exactly three episodes over the course of my editorship, which I’ve arbitrarily decided is not enough to qualify, and b) Game of Thrones is awesome. In Westeros, subtlety takes a back seat: there’s graphic sex and violence in equal parts, more than a couple totally abhorrent characters, and also dragons and zombies. And at the center is Tyrion Lannister, probably the best fantasy-epic character I’ve ever encountered.</p>
<p>That’s all I’ve got. Thanks, a lot, for reading.</p>

